BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (FOR PARENTS: HOW TO USE THIS SYSTEM) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.0 Td (This system works because it gives kids OWNERSHIP over their screen time instead of making) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.0 Td (you the 'screen police.' When kids understand the rules, help track their own time, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.0 Td (earn screen privileges - battles decrease dramatically.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 634.2 Td (THE 4 COMPONENTS:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 618.2 Td (- 1. FAMILY RULES \(pages 3-5\): Establish clear, visual boundaries) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 604.2 Td (- 2. EARN IT SYSTEM \(pages 6-12\): Tasks completed before screens) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 590.2 Td (- 3. TRACKING \(pages 13-20\): Kids self-monitor with parent verification) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 576.2 Td (- 4. ALTERNATIVES \(pages 21-30\): 100 activities to replace screen time) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 548.4 Td (AAP RECOMMENDED LIMITS:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 532.4 Td (Ages 2-5: Max 1 hour/day of high-quality programming \(with adult\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 518.4 Td (Ages 6-12: Consistent limits, prioritize sleep, activity, homework first) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 504.4 Td (All ages: No screens 1 hour before bed, no screens during meals) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 480.6 Td (TIP: Laminate pages 3-6 and hang them where kids can see daily!) Tj ET
endstream
